<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>18421</id>
	<title>ap_regexec function declaration arg1 should be const</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">In httpd.h, arg1 of the ap_regexec function should be declared const.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">The code
should change from:
AP_DECLARE(int)    ap_regexec(regex_t *preg, const char *string,
                              size_t nmatch, regmatch_t pmatch[], int eflags);
to:
AP_DECLARE(int)    ap_regexec(const regex_t *preg, const char *string,
                              size_t nmatch, regmatch_t pmatch[], int eflags);</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">When executing a regular expression, the regex_t structure is not modified by
regexec (see the regexec man page).</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">My compiler gives warning messages when passing "const regex_t *" to ap_regexec,
even though it's perfectly valid to use "const regex_t *" instead of "regex_t *".</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
